# versions.env — single source of truth for pinned tool / runtime
# versions (SPEC-009, docs/plans/SPEC-009-plan.md §"versions.env の設計").
#
# Format is plain `KEY=value` (no quotes, no `export`, no inline
# comments after a value) so this one file is consumable by all of:
#   - a shell:           set -a; . ./.devcontainer/versions.env; set +a
#   - GitHub Actions:     cat .devcontainer/versions.env >> "$GITHUB_ENV"
#   - docker compose:     docker compose --env-file .devcontainer/versions.env ...
#   - make:               include .devcontainer/versions.env   (or a $(shell ...) parse)
#
# .devcontainer/toolchain/Dockerfile receives every value below as a build ARG
# (wired through .devcontainer/compose.tools.yml's `build.args`, which itself reads
# these via `${VAR}` compose variable substitution from this file). Once
# Phase C (CI) lands, .github/workflows/*.yml loads this same file into
# $GITHUB_ENV instead of hardcoding versions in each workflow's own
# `env:` block — do not let the two drift.
#
# Bumping a version: edit it here only, then rebuild the toolchain image
# (`docker compose --env-file .devcontainer/versions.env -f .devcontainer/compose.tools.yml build`).

# --- Promoted from .github/workflows/cicd.yml's `env:` block ---------------
# (SPEC-009 R1). BUN_VERSION is deliberately unified to 1.3.14 here: prior
# to this file, cicd.yml pinned bun 1.2.21 while contract-drift.yml pinned
# 1.3.14 on purpose ("intentionally different from cicd") and
# app/web/Dockerfile floats the major (`oven/bun:1`). A single polyglot
# toolchain image cannot carry two bun versions, so this repo now runs on
# one: 1.3.14 (the newer of the two CI pins; already proven to work by
# contract-drift.yml). app/web/Dockerfile's runtime image pin is out of
# SPEC-009's scope (§3 スコープ外: 既存アプリ runtime イメージの設計変更) and is
# left as-is, so a residual toolchain/runtime bun version gap remains --
# tracked as a risk in docs/plans/SPEC-009-plan.md.
GO_VERSION=1.26
BUN_VERSION=1.3.14
GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION=2.12.2
TERRAFORM_VERSION=1.10.5
TFLINT_VERSION=v0.55.1
# NOT v0.58.1 (.github/workflows/cicd.yml's current pin, matched here for
# every other tool above). Confirmed during Phase A image-build
# verification (2026-07-10) that aquasecurity/trivy has deleted the
# GitHub Release (and its binary/checksums.txt assets) for v0.58.1 --
# `GET /repos/aquasecurity/trivy/releases/tags/v0.58.1` 404s, as does
# every other tag in the v0.27.0-v0.69.1 range; only pre-v0.27.0 and
# v0.69.2+ releases still have their assets. .devcontainer/toolchain/Dockerfile
# installs trivy from these release assets (aquasecurity's own official
# install script), so a deleted-upstream version cannot be built here
# regardless of image design. v0.69.2 is the nearest still-resolvable
# release to the original v0.58.1 pin (same "adjust to the nearest
# resolvable version, document why" precedent app/api/Makefile already
# set for SQLC_VERSION above it). cicd.yml's own TRIVY_VERSION pin will
# need the same fix in Phase C (impl-ci) for the `iac` job's
# aquasecurity/setup-trivy@v0.2.3 step to keep working -- flagged to
# admin/user as a residual item, since it is a preexisting break in this
# repo unrelated to SPEC-009 itself.
TRIVY_VERSION=v0.69.2
POSTGRES_VERSION=17.5-alpine

# --- sqlc / goose / swag / goimports CLIs baked into .devcontainer/toolchain ------
# Previously each of these had its own "source of truth" scattered across
# app/{api,auth,migrator}/Makefile (see those files' own comments, which
# still cross-reference this file). SPEC-009 consolidates the version
# strings here because .devcontainer/toolchain/Dockerfile now needs to `go
# install` these same exact versions at image-build time (see that
# Dockerfile's header comment) -- keeping the version in two places would
# drift. Each Go stack's Makefile reads the version string from here
# (`include .../versions.env` or equivalent) instead of hardcoding it.
#
# NOTE for Phase B: `go run pkg@version` does NOT work offline even with
# the module fully cached (verified during Phase A -- see
# .devcontainer/toolchain/Dockerfile's own comment); each Makefile must invoke
# these tools by their installed binary name (`sqlc`/`goose`/`swag`/
# `goimports`, already on PATH in every toolchain image) instead, so the
# version strings below are consumed only to keep this file, the
# Dockerfile's `go install`, and each Makefile's own documentation in
# sync -- not to build a `go run pkg@<version>` invocation string.
#
# Do not bump SQLC_VERSION/GOOSE_VERSION here without also checking
# .claude/rules/db.md's "版" section and app/migrator/go.mod's
# github.com/pressly/goose/v3 require (goose is a *library* dependency
# there, unlike the CLI usage everywhere else -- the two must stay in
# sync per that module's own Makefile comment).
SQLC_VERSION=v1.31.1
GOOSE_VERSION=v3.24.1
SWAG_VERSION=v2.0.0-rc5

# golang.org/x/tools/cmd/goimports. Previously `@latest` in all three Go
# Makefiles (app/api, app/auth, app/migrator) -- resolving `@latest`
# needs network and is non-reproducible, which SPEC-009 R3's
# `--network none` exec phase cannot tolerate, so this pins an exact
# version instead.
#
# v0.42.0 is pinned for reproducibility under SPEC-009's offline exec phase.
# Its go.mod requires `go 1.24.0` (≤ GO_VERSION above); newer x/tools
# releases from v0.43.0 onward require `go 1.25.0`+ and may be bumped
# later without functional need.
GOIMPORTS_VERSION=v0.42.0
